abcfamilymedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=3120777&type=peck WebCite query result]</ref>\n* [[Elvis Perkins]], singer, son of actor [[Anthony Perkins]]\n* [[Ben Platt (actor)|Ben Platt]], Broadway and film actor\n* [[Jason Reitman]], Golden Globe-winning screenwriter, director<ref>[http://www.biography.com/articles/Jason-Reitman-267538 Jason Reitman Biography \u2013 Biography.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100623063326/http://www.biography.com/articles/Jason-Reitman-267538 |date=June 23, 2010 }}</ref>\n* [[Sally Ride]], astronaut<ref name=\"LATimes\"/>\n* [[Josh Satin]], retired major league baseball player \n* [[Andrea Savage]], actress\n* [[Jason Segel]], actor, screenwriter<ref>{{cite web | author = &#151;Jason Segel | url = http://www.biography.com/people/jason-segel-20701895 | title = Jason Segel Biography \u2013 | publisher = Biography.com | date =  | accessdate = May 16, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510014309/http://www.biography.com/people/jason-segel-20701895 |archive-date=May 10, 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Ben Sherwood]], president of [[ABC News]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.hw.com/alumni/News/tabid/1515/ctl/ArticleView/mid/4169/articleId/5828/Ben-Sherwood-81-Named-President-of-ABC-News.aspx | title = Ben Sherwood '81 Named President of ABC News | date = December 3, 2010 | work = Harvard-Westlake School Alumni News | accessdate = May 11, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105211457/http://www.hw.com/alumni/News/tabid/1515/ctl/ArticleView/mid/4169/articleId/5828/Ben-Sherwood-81-Named-President-of-ABC-News.aspx|archive-date=November 5, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Jacob Soboroff]] journalist and correspondent, NBC News and MSNBC\n* [[Tori Spelling]], actress<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.biography.com/people/tori-spelling-443558 | title = Tori Spelling Biography \u2013 | publisher = Biography.com | date =  | accessdate = May 16, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120711085315/http://www.biography.com/people/tori-spelling-443558 |archive-date=July 11, 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Alex Stepheson]], professional basketball player\n* [[Erik Swoope]], NFL player\n* [[David Talbot]], journalist, author, media entrepreneur<ref>{{cite news | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2007/may/30/entertainment/et-talbot30 | title = JFK, RFK and the brother of all conspiracy theories | last = Abcarian | first = Robin | date = May 30, 2007 | work = Los Angeles Times | accessdate = May 11, 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Stephen Talbot]], child actor; documentary filmmaker, PBS ''Frontline''<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.kqed.org/arts/13809968/jerry-mathers-died-steve-talbot | title = The Day the Beaver Died | date = October 1, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Shirley Temple]], actress, diplomat<ref>{{cite web | author = &#151;Shirley Temple | url = http://www.biography.com/people/shirley-temple-9503798 | title = Shirley Temple Biography \u2013 | publisher = Biography.com | date =  | accessdate = May 16, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Dara Torres]], swimmer and [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] [[medal]]ist<ref>{{cite news | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2008/aug/16/sports/sp-olydowney16 | title = She's propelled by dad's memory | last = Downey | first = Mike | date = August 16, 2008 | work = Los Angeles Times | accessdate = May 11, 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Nik Turley]], baseball player<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.silive.com/siyankees/index.ssf/2010/07/staten_island_yankees_defeat_c.html | title = Staten Island Yankees defeat Connecticut Tigers behind southpaw Nik Turley, 6\u20133 | publisher = SILive.com | date =  | accessdate = September 18, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Dorothy Wang]], socialite; actress, ''Rich Kids of Beverly Hills''{{citation needed|reason=linked article does not mention this school|date=May 2018}}\n* [[Matthew Weiner]], writer, creator of ''[[Mad Men]]''<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Sarah Nilsen, Sarah E. Turner | title = The Colorblind Screen: Television 