{"title_page": "Simon Templeman", "text_new": "{{short description|British actor}}\n{{BLP sources|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=November 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image = SimonTempleman.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Templeman in December 2008\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1954|1|2|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web | first =Stanley| last = Wells| title = Shakespeare Survey Volume 47: Playing Places for Shakespeare | publisher = Cambridge University Press | year= 1994| isbn= 9781139053228 }}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Sussex]], England\n| occupation = Actor\n| years active = 1983\u2013present\n| spouse = [[Rosalind Chao]]\n| children = 2\n}}\n\n'''Simon Templeman''' (born 2 January 1954), also known as '''Simon Templeton''', is an English actor known for his roles as [[Kain (Legacy of Kain)|Kain]] in the video game series ''[[Legacy of Kain]]'', as [[Loghain Mac Tir]] in the ''[[Dragon Age]]'' series, and as Jacob Danik, the main antagonist in the video game ''[[Dead Space 3]]''. He was a series regular on ''[[The Neighbors (2012 TV series)|The Neighbors]]'', an [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] sitcom.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/ustv/a381828/the-neighbors-abcs-new-alien-sitcom-watch-video/|title='The Neighbors': ABC sitcom - video|last=Jeffery|first=Morgan|date=2012-05-15|website=Digital Spy|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\nTempleman also gained fame playing the Angel of Death on the TV series ''[[Charmed]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/charmed-things-wrong-with-halliwell-sisters-we-ignore/|title=Charmed: 20 Things Wrong With The Halliwell Sisters We All Choose To Ignore|date=2019-02-13|website=ScreenRant|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nHe is married to actress [[Rosalind Chao]], with whom he has two children.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://showbizgeek.com/what-ever-happened-to-the-cast-of-star-trek-the-next-generation |title=What Ever Happened To\u2026 the cast of Star Trek: The Next Generation? |first=Rory |last=John |website=Showbiz Geek |date=2014-01-17 |access-date=2019-09-22 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150524142635/http://showbizgeek.com/what-ever-happened-to-the-cast-of-star-trek-the-next-generation/ |archivedate=2015-05-24 }}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Animation===\n{| class = \"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class = \"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''[[TaleSpin]]'' \n| Rick Sky\n| Episode: \"Bygones\"\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''[[James Bond Jr.]]'' \n| Trevor Noseworthy IV\n|<ref name=\"James Bond Jr.(1991)\">List of cast {{cite web |title=James Bond Jr.(1991) |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0283744/fullcredits#cast |publisher= [[IMDb]] |accessdate=28 August 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1991\u201393\n| ''[[The Legend of Prince Valiant]]'' \n| Sir [[Mordred]]\n|\n|-\n| 1994\u201395\n| ''[[Fantastic Four (1994 TV series)|Fantastic Four]]'' \n| [[Doctor Doom]]\n| Third voice, Season 2 only\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[Biker Mice from Mars]]''\n| Sir Mordred\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 1996\u201397\n| ''[[The Incredible Hulk (1996 TV series)|The Incredible Hulk]]'' \n| Doctor Doom\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2001\u201315\n| ''[[Totally Spies!]]'' \n| Dr. Gelee\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2005\u201306\n| ''[[Loonatics Unleashed]]'' \n| Dr. Dare\n| 2 episodes\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class = \"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class = \"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1983\n| ''[[The Professionals (TV series)|The Professionals]]''\n| Neville Grant\n| Episode: \"Cry Wolf\"\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[Star Trek: The Next Generation]]''\n| John Bates\n| Episode: \"[[The Defector (TNG episode)|The Defector]]\"<br>His wife [[Rosalind Chao]], played [[Keiko O'Brien]] in several episodes\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[Father Dowling Mysteries]]''\n| Foster\n| Episode: \"The Legacy Mystery\"\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[Melrose Place]]''\n| Kurt\n| Episode: \"For Love of Money\"\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Moo