hs]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Bergamo]]\n[[Category:Italian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Lombardy]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|the troubadour|Paolo Lanfranchi da Pistoia}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name        = Paolo Lanfranchi\n| image       =\n| caption     =\n| fullname    = Paolo Lanfranchi\n| nickname    =\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1968|07|25}}\n| birth_place = [[Gazzaniga]], [[Italy]]\n| height      =\n| weight      =\n| currentteam = Retired\n| discipline  = [[Road bicycle racing|Road]]\n| role        = Rider\n| ridertype   = All-rounder\n| proyears1   = 1993-1994\n| proteam1    = {{ct|UNO|1993}}\n| proyears2   = 1995\n| proteam2    = {{ct|BRE|1995}}\n| proyears3   = 1996\n| proteam3    = [[San Marco Group]]\n| proyears4   = 1996\u20132001\n| proteam4    = {{ct|MAP|1996}}\n| proyears5   = 2002\n| proteam5    = [[Index\u2013Alexia Alluminio]]\n| proyears6   = 2003\u20132004\n| proteam6    = {{ct|CSF|2003}}\n| majorwins   = [[Tour de Langkawi]] (1999 & 2001)\n}}\n\n'''Paolo Lanfranchi''' (born July 25, 1968 in [[Gazzaniga]], [[Province of Bergamo]]) is an [[Italians|Italian]] former professional [[road bicycle racer]]. Originally from [[Gazzaniga]], [[Italy]]. Lanfranchi was a dominating figure in the [[Italy|Italian]] road racing scene by winning many points standings. Turning pro in 1993, he captured his first major victory in winning a [[Yellow Jersey]] for [[General classification]] of the [[Tour de Langkawi]] in 1999 riding for the {{ct|MAP|1999}} team, and again in 2001 with the same team.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/paolo-lanfranchi | title=Paolo Lanfranchi | work=ProCyclingStats | accessdate=20 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Major results ==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n;1988\n: 1st [[GP Capodarco]]\n;1990\n